  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishing a centre of excellence for Conflict and Stabilisation activity related to fragile and conflict affected states.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide a centre of excellence for stabilisation and conflict related activity, enabling the UK to deliver more integrated and effective results in Fragile and Conflict Affected States (FCAS).To provide a centre of excellence for Conflict and Stabilisation related activity which will enable the UK to deliver more integrated and effective results in Fragile and Conflict Affected States (FCAS) by: Strengthening HMG conflict and stabilisation activity in high and medium priority countries. Providing appropriate training and technical support to HMG staff and Deployable Civilian Experts enabling effective operation in priority fragile and conflict affected states and improved use of Conflict Pool resources.Establishing a pool of Senior Conflict and Stabilisation Advisers.Providing expertise, best-practice and lessons to develop more coherent and effective conflict and stabilisation policy, strategy, programming and training.</narrative>
  </description>
